  "text": "The translation ZToPP can be used to formally define the semantics of compositions of Z specifications and predicative specifications, by translating heterogeneous specifications into a homogeneous specification. In this paper, heterogeneous specifications are given a semantics in terms of predicative notation. Details of how the translation process operates over combinators are in [CITATION_1] . Informally, ZToPP applies partwise over predicative combinators. Therefore, we always write Z specifications under the assumption that we can translate them into predicative notation. While we have checked that translation is possible for the specifications in this paper, we do not show the checking in the case studies.",
